This is a rust project with crates in the crates dir:
rook: the main code for rook, contains all the core logic
rook-acp: the agent client protocol implementation
rook-acp-macros: macros for the agent client protocol
rook-cli: the command line interface, uses rook crate
rook-mcp: the mcp servers that ship with rook
rook-sdk: the sdk for building extensions or embedding rook
rook-test-support: utilities for testing rook


ui/rook has a tauri-based desktop app in typescript.

non trivial features should be implemented in the rook crate and then be called from the rook-cli crate for the cli. for the desktop, you want to interact with the backend via tauri commands or the sdk.

tips: 
- can look at unstaged changes for what is being worked on if starting
- always check rust compiles, cargo fmt etc and `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` (as well as run tests in files you are working on)
- in ui/rook, look at how you can run lint checks and if other tests can run
